==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pharyngotomy
<hw>Phar`yn*got"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pharynx</ets> + Gr. <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut: cf. F.
<ets>pharyngotomie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The operation of making an incision into the pharynx, to remove a
tumor or anything that obstructs the passage.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Scarification or incision of the tonsils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharynx</ent>⟦br⟧
